03:44.042 --> 03:45.083
Lila.

03:52.375 --> 03:53.917
You're in the hospital.

03:55.500 --> 03:57.625
You had an accident, but everything's OK.

03:59.167 --> 04:01.167
You're fine, don't worry.

04:06.875 --> 04:08.042
Lila, sweetheart.

04:10.875 --> 04:12.333
Do you know who I am?

04:16.583 --> 04:18.083
Do you know your name?

05:10.583 --> 05:11.625
Hi.

05:12.875 --> 05:14.167
I'm Blanca.

05:15.750 --> 05:17.458
I'm a friend of yours.

05:19.583 --> 05:23.125
Yesterday I went to your house
to talk to you about work.

05:25.333 --> 05:28.000
While I made calls,
you went down to the beach.

05:29.917 --> 05:32.042
You were taking too long,
so I went to look for you.

05:33.875 --> 05:36.625
Then I saw you'd fainted
in the water.

05:42.625 --> 05:43.917
Do you like it?

05:47.708 --> 05:48.833
I make them myself.

05:52.375 --> 05:54.292
I can teach you, if you want.

05:57.500 --> 06:01.417
It's easier to undo it,
and then redo it again.

06:02.542 --> 06:05.958
We can follow the pattern
and make it like it was before.

06:14.042 --> 06:15.333
Do you know who it is?

06:17.042 --> 06:18.042
It's...

06:19.333 --> 06:20.375
Shakira.

06:42.500 --> 06:44.042
Do you know who she is?

06:49.833 --> 06:50.958
Lily.

06:54.958 --> 06:56.125
Lila Cassen.

07:26.083 --> 07:27.458
Don't worry, Lila.

07:47.708 --> 07:49.125
Who are you?

07:50.042 --> 07:51.333
I'm Blanca.

07:53.458 --> 07:56.000
- You're Blanca.
- That's right.

07:56.292 --> 07:58.000
- Are you my friend?
- Yes.

08:00.000 --> 08:02.500
- Do I have a house?
- Of course.

08:07.250 --> 08:09.125
Then I want to go home.

09:02.875 --> 09:08.375
WHO WILL SING TO YOU

09:36.708 --> 09:38.167
Did you picture it like this?

09:39.833 --> 09:41.125
I didn't picture anything.

09:42.875 --> 09:44.250
It will be just the two of us.

09:45.000 --> 09:47.542
I told César
to take some time off.

09:48.083 --> 09:50.250
- Who's César?
- Your personal assistant.

09:51.500 --> 09:53.708
A house like this
needs people to take care of it.

09:54.167 --> 09:56.417
While he's gone,
I'll take care of everything.

09:57.708 --> 09:59.625
I'm going to make something to eat.

10:00.042 --> 10:01.500
Do you want some crudités?

10:01.792 --> 10:02.875
Some what?

10:03.208 --> 10:04.708
Some crudités.

10:06.042 --> 10:09.375
Raw vegetables.
Carrots, celery, cucumber. Raw.

10:09.792 --> 10:10.958
Why raw?

10:11.708 --> 10:12.988
Because you're a raw food vegan.

10:13.125 --> 10:14.792
- I'm what?
- A raw food vegan.

10:15.583 --> 10:19.250
You eat raw things because
you think it's better for your body.

10:20.042 --> 10:21.458
Meat, too?

10:22.250 --> 10:24.333
You don't eat meat.

10:25.292 --> 10:27.542
Want me
to make you something else?

10:29.500 --> 10:30.750
A fried egg?

10:31.958 --> 10:34.083
OK, I'm going to the kitchen.

10:34.708 --> 10:35.958
Take a look around the house.

10:36.000 --> 10:37.625
- I'll get you in a bit.
- Blanca.

10:38.083 --> 10:39.333
Yes?

10:40.083 --> 10:41.250
Where's the bathroom?

12:13.458 --> 12:14.738
What did you want to talk about?

12:15.917 --> 12:16.917
What?

12:17.250 --> 12:20.000
Before I went to the beach
and you found me in the water.

12:20.625 --> 12:23.792
You said you came to talk about work.

12:24.833 --> 12:25.833
But...

12:26.625 --> 12:28.042
I'm retired.

12:29.333 --> 12:31.583
You don't have
to worry about that right now.

12:31.750 --> 12:33.750
When should I start worrying?

12:37.000 --> 12:39.667
I planned to wait
a few days to discuss it.

12:41.458 --> 12:42.458
I...

12:44.208 --> 12:45.958
I'd rather discuss it now.

12:47.583 --> 12:48.583
OK.

12:54.000 --> 12:55.833
You haven't sung in ten years.

12:57.833 --> 13:01.833
You've just been
living off of album royalties,

13:01.958 --> 13:03.333
but that's not so easy now.

13:03.833 --> 13:06.750
Without doing concerts, it's almost
impossible to live off of music.

13:06.917 --> 13:09.167
Or at least, live this way.

13:10.208 --> 13:13.125
So we scheduled
your return to the stage.

13:13.542 --> 13:15.500
Ten concerts, for now.

13:15.917 --> 13:18.417
The first is in two months, in Madrid.

13:22.125 --> 13:24.083
What if I don't sing again?

13:27.917 --> 13:29.958
First, you'd have to sell this house.

13:31.042 --> 13:32.875
Then there are several options.

13:33.000 --> 13:36.333
You could disappear,
start a new life away from it all.

13:36.750 --> 13:39.083
Or make a living on talk shows.

13:39.750 --> 13:41.583
Lots of singers end up doing that.

13:42.083 --> 13:45.083
But it's because they need to,
and you don't.

13:45.417 --> 13:48.042
- Why not?
- Because you have talent.

13:50.708 --> 13:52.542
Then why did I stop singing?

13:55.125 --> 13:56.792
Because your mother died.

14:02.583 --> 14:04.167
I've been with you for 25 years.

14:04.458 --> 14:06.125
I'm not leaving you now.

14:08.167 --> 14:09.875
No one matters to me as much as you.

14:11.167 --> 14:13.042
No one matters more to me
than Lila Cassen.

